.TH GIT-PR-CHECKS 1 "2026-06-14" "git-tools" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
git-pr-checks \- summarize GitHub pull request checks
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B git pr-checks
.RI [ options ]
.RI [ number|url|branch ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B git pr-checks
summarizes GitHub pull request checks. Without a target, it uses the pull
request for the current branch.
.PP
The command preserves useful GitHub CLI status semantics: passing checks return
0, pending checks return 8, and failing, cancelled, or missing checks return 1.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-porcelain
Print stable
.B key=value
summary fields followed by tab-separated
.B check
records.
.TP
.BR \-\-required-only ", " \-\-required
Only include checks required by branch protection.
.TP
.BR \-w ", " \-\-watch
Wait for checks to finish before summarizing.
.TP
.BI "\-i, \-\-interval " seconds
Refresh interval in seconds for
.BR \-\-watch .
The default is 10.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show help.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Checks passed.
.TP
.B 1
Checks failed, were cancelled, are missing, or could not be read.
.TP
.B 2
Usage or local environment error.
.TP
.B 8
Checks are still pending.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR git-pr-ready (1),
.BR git-pr-stack (1)
